Well a bit more /scouring/ of the Internet along with some /trial and error=
/
and I have eventually arrived :-)

Here is how it is done. I launch the t=
est case with the JAVA debugger
options and make sure to set the suspend op=
tion to yes. This way it waits
for the debugger to make the connection befo=
re executing the test. I use a
script to search for the  test case and set =
the classpath.

java -Xdebug -Xnoagent
-Djava.compiler=3DNONE-Xrunjdwp:tran=
sport=3Ddt_socket,server=3Dy,suspend=3Dy,address=3D4001
-classpath
$CLASSPA=
TH $FULL_PACKAGE

I set the breakpoint in my test case before connecting re=
motely with the
debugger and &quot;Bob&#39;s your Uncle&quot; we are away debugging (remo=
tely).

I hope that this will be useful for others ...
Kind regards,
David.=



